Zandile Christmas Mafe, a suspect in connection to a fire at the South African Parliament, appears at the magistrate's court in Cape Town. AFP/Gianluigi Guercia JOHANNESBURG - Alleged Parliament arsonist, Zandile Mafe, has been released from Valkenberg Psychiatric Hospital. He was sent there for a mental evaluation. READ: Order to send Zandile Mafe to psychiatric hospital set aside Mafe has been transferred to Pollsmoor Prison.  The man accused of setting Parliament alight was ordered to undergo a psychiatric assessment. It came after a submission by a prosecutor that he had a mental condition. Mafe, however, launched a legal bid to overturn the order. READ: Parliament Fire | Zandile Mafe charged with terrorism The Western Cape High Court granted the application. Mafe will remain in custody at Pollsmoor Prison until his bail hearing this weekend.